- Use `dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ProblemDetails` to install the necessary NuGet package.
- Configure Problem Details in your `Startup.cs` or `Program.cs`:
  ```csharp
  services.AddControllers().AddProblemDetails(options =>
  {
      options.IncludeExceptionDetails = (ctx, ex) => ctx.Environment.IsDevelopment();
  });
  ```
- Handle validation errors using `ValidationProblemDetailsFactory`:
  ```csharp
  [ApiController]
  public class MyController : ControllerBase
  {
      private readonly ValidationProblemDetailsFactory _problemDetailsFactory;

      public MyController(ValidationProblemDetailsFactory problemDetailsFactory)
      {
          _problemDetailsFactory = problemDetailsFactory;
      }

      [HttpPost("validate")]
      public IActionResult Validate([FromBody] MyModel model)
      {
          if (!ModelState.IsValid)
              return new BadRequestObjectResult(_problemDetailsFactory.CreateValidationProblemDetails(HttpContext, ModelState));

          // Proceed with valid data
          return Ok();
      }
  }
  ```
- Ensure your API responses are in a machine-readable format as per RFC 7807.
